ole affair went by quickly, and in a few weeks, I already owned an apartment. An 80 percent mortgage financed it. I had to borrow the remaining twenty percent in a consumer loan at the same bank. The mortgage with a three-year fixation at that time had an interest rate of 3.2% per annum, but the bank offered me the option of reducing interest rates if I bought other products from them that I don\u2019t even need."), mdx("h2", {
